Generative AI with SAP and Amazon Bedrock Utilizing GenAI with SAP and AWS Business Use Cases — Miguel Figueiredo 
SAP Use-case- tracker for repos and knowledge 
https://github.com/SAP-samples/btp-cap-genai-rag 
Official SAP sample for building genAI integrated applications.  
Architecture (how it works): 
 
User opens the chat app on phone/computer ⏩ Application router (for authorization) ⏩ then SAPUI5 opens (the face/ chat window) ⏩ type ur query/ question ⏩ the question goes to the brain ”SAP CAP Service” ⏩ the first stop is SAP HANA CLOUD where it uses vector engine in the first attempt to find things related to query(grounding process) ⏩ now the next path is to look into the ”Destination Service” to find the secret and secure path to LLM ⏩ then it enters the Generative AI hub . Inside this the orchestrator takes the files and does ”Data Masking” (removes any confidential information so that the AI neve sees it like credit card info,keys etc) ->”Templating” (arranging the resources to draft a clear prompt to the llm) ->  the orchestration now passes thsi grounded prompt to foundation models ⏩ The end result. 
 
How this helps with our chatbot usecase: 
* This repo is the Orchestrator/MCP Client, this is the RAG part (using HANA vector engine) 
Next steps : 
1. Create an SAP Destination Service (this will have the secure address (the Odata API URL) for our system) 
 
2.  Add this new function in our CAP Service code (ex: check_live_sales : when user gives an order number, I should use S/4 HANA Destination Service to look into live system and get status)  
Link:- GitHub - CostingGeek/sap-mcp: An MCP server to retrieve information like Sales Orders from the SAP … 
Approach:- This repository contains a Python-based solution that enables bidirectional communication between Claude (Anthropic's large language model) and SAP systems via the SAP Graph API. By leveraging the Model Context Protocol (MCP), this integration allows Claude to retrieve and process SAP business data in real-time. Claude could be changed to other LLMs as per the usecase. 
 
Link:- GitHub - tqtensor/pythonizesap: Automatic data extraction from SAP by using Python 
Approach:- GuiXT is used for simplifying and customizing the SAP GUI, while SAP GUI Scripting allows for recording and replaying user interactions, which can then be integrated with Python. This approach currently does not include MCP. 
Activating GuiXT 
 Link:- GitHub - GutjahrAI/sap-odata-mcp-py: Yet Another Python Based SAP MCP Server
Apporach:- Implements a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that enables AI assistants to interact with SAP OData services. The above approach automatically finds the available OData services, locates entities across multiple services, provides CRUD support, follows a batch operating strategy, and effective error handling. 
 Link:- GitHub - CDataSoftware/sap-erp-mcp-server-by-cdata: This read-only MCP Server allows you to connect… 
Approach:- This MCP Server allows you to connect to SAP ERP data from Claude Desktop through CData JDBC Drivers and provides full CRUD functionality. 
RAG using Azure: 
To integrate RAG into our application, we can make use of agentic retrieval in Azure cloud platform, a specialized pipeline designed specifically for RAG patterns.   
What we need: one or more knowledge sources, a knowledge agent, and the retrieve action that you call from application code, such as a tool that works with your agent. 
Classic RAG integation: 
Start with a user question or request (prompt). 
Send it as a query request to Azure AI Search to find relevant information. 
Return the top-ranked search results to an LLM. 
Use the natural language understanding and reasoning capabilities of the LLM to generate a response to the initial prompt. 
 RAG and generative AI - Azure AI Search | Microsoft Learn 
Blog for implementing RAG in azure environments 
 azure-search-openai-demo/README.md at main · Azure-Samples/azure-search-openai-demo 
Github repo (demo) for implementing RAG concepts in Azure environments 
